CatDescriptText: Mr. Ronald Sieber, salesman, Bridgeville, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 27, 1962, pg. 12 with question: "What is the most important issue confronting Pittsburgh in 1962?" Answer reads: "I wonder if someone can stop the filthy literature which comes out on out newstands and is made available so easily for the young kids.  Also, we should do something about the immoral movies which are to easily available."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Ronald Sieber wearing diagonally striped necktie and tweed coat, standing in front of Bud Saunders Flowers awning, Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
